 poems by Goethe, Rellstab, and Heine. He deconstructs Winterreise, using its convoluted origins to illuminate its textual contradictions. Finally, Kramer scrutinizes settings from the Abendrote cycle (on poems by Friedrich Schlegel) for signs of cyclic process. Probing the farthest reaches of Schubert's engagement with the poetics of lieder, Distant Cycles exposes tensions between Schubert the composer and Schubert the merchant-entrepreneur.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aSong cyclesxHistory and criticismxCriticism, interpretation, etcxManuscripts. 0aSong cyclesxHistory and criticism. 0aSongsy19th centuryxAnalysis, appreciation. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package Archive 1990-1999z978311066785140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226452333423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226452333.jpg  a978-3-11-066785-1  UChP eBook-Package Archive 1990-1999c1990d1999  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles